    "The validation loss decreases gradually from 0.85 to around 0.25 without much deviation from the training loss curve, which is good generalization to unseen data.",
    "This behavior is a consequence of the key techniques implemented, which Table 9.",
    "The ablation study alternatives.",
    "include dropout with a dropout rate of 0.3, early stopping in case there is stagnation in the validation loss, and extensive data augmentation methods in the form of rotation, flipping, and zooming.",
    "The minimal difference between the training and validation loss means that the model does not overfit to the train data, hence the higher performance during testing."
